1.9	We recommended and Management agreed to the following:
a.	Update or recreate Inventory Committee and mobilize additional competent personnel from other departments as members and completely conduct physical count of Inventory of the Municipality’s PPE annually and submit to the Office of the Auditor the duly accomplished RPCPPE of all PPE accounts;
b.	Direct the Municipal Accountant and designate General Services Officer reconcile and analyze the difference between ledger and RPCPPE report and effect necessary adjustments;
c.	Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC) and Property Cards for each group of PPEs, respectively and reconciliation between these two records shall be undertaken regularly;
d.	Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to start the reclassification process of the properties that have cost of ₱50,000.00 and below. The Municipal Accountant likewise make necessary adjustments by: a) debiting Prior Period Adjustments and crediting appropriate PPE account for reclassification; and b) debiting Accumulated Depreciation and crediting Prior Period Adjustments for closing of previously recognized accumulated depreciation;
e.	Require the Municipal Accountant and GSO that the existing AREs of properties that cost ₱50,000.00 and below, except for low-valued semi-expendable property shall be replaced by ICS; and
f.	In response to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, create an Inventory Committee for the sole purpose of conducting a one-time cleansing of the Municipality’s PPE which shall be composed of adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory.

