1.22 	We recommended and Management agreed to the following:
Update or recreate Inventory Committee and mobilize additional competent personnel from other departments as members and completely conduct physical count of Inventory of the Municipality’s PPE annually and submit to the Office of the Auditor the duly accomplished RPCPPE of all PPE accounts;
Direct the Municipal Accountant and designate General Services Officer reconcile and analyze the difference between ledger and RPCPPE report and effect necessary adjustments;
Require the Municipal Accountant and the Designate GSO-Designate maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC) and Property Cards for each group of PPEs, respectively and reconciliation between these two records shall be undertaken regularly;
Require the Accounting Office exert extra effort to look for the available documents of the unidentified beginning balances of CIP account and make necessary adjustments thereafter;
To require the Municipal Accountant reclassify the fully completed projects with cost aggregating to ₱39.723 million from CIP to its appropriate Asset account; and
In response to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, create an Inventory Committee for the sole purpose of conducting a one-time cleansing of the Municipality’s PPE which shall be composed of adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory.

Require the BAC to undergo procurement process in hiring consultants of which all documentary requirements needed in evaluating the qualifications of the consultants such as Professional License, Term of Reference and other requirements on the expertise and qualifications necessary for the understanding be submitted as required in Section 2 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184;

Require the Municipal Budget Officer to include Consultancy Services in the Annual Procurement Plan;

Require the Municipal Accountant to see to it that the detailed accomplishments report was attached in every claim of the consultancy services;

Stop hiring consultants for doing job that does not require the level of expertise of attention of a consultant but instead let the regular or job order employee with the same function of duties will do the job;

Require the Human Resource Department to make an assessment whether the purpose for hiring consultants was achieved by preparing Consultancy Progress Reports and submit the same to the Local Chief Executive. Ensure that the duties stated on COS were aligned on actual services rendered; and

See to it that all contracts and documents forming part thereof be submitted to the Office of the Auditor within five days from the date of execution.

Management require the concerned personnel to subject the damaged parts of the property to pre-repair evaluation and inspections before requisition for replacement and the replaced parts to post-repair inspection by the designated LGU inspector to ascertain that the property is in operational and the part requested were all installed;

Require the preparation of Waste Material Reports for the damaged replaced part and have is inspected before disposal is made; and

The Municipal Accountant cautiously check the completeness of all the pertinent supporting documents before allowing the payment.

We recommended and the Management agreed:
To review composition of Inventory Committee and mobilize competent and responsible personnel as members of the Inventory Committee to conduct completely physical count of the Municipality’s PPE annually, prepare reports and to submit the duly accomplished RPCPPE to the Auditor;
To direct the Municipal Accountant and designated General Services Officer religiously maintain the PPELC and Stock Cards/Property Cards;
To direct the Municipal Accountant and designated General Services Officer to reconcile and analyzed the difference between their respective and effect necessary adjustments; and
To instruct the Inventory and Appraisal Committee to give extra effort in determining the vital information needed of the unserviceable properties and conduct disposal process thru auction or sale thereof to generate additional income considering that the non-operating assets are subject to further deterioration and diminishing market value.

We recommended that:

1. Management maintain property and subsidiary ledger cards and prepare/reconcile same with the RPCPPE;



2. Management appropriate fund for the titling of all land; 


3.	The LCE direct the Municipal Assessor̕ s Office to exert effort in titling the land owned by the Municipality;


4. The LCE require the Accounting Office to set up and maintain complete accounting records; and,




5. The LCE require the Treasurer̕ s Office/GSO to keep on file complete records of real properties.

